com.here.platform.location.core.graph.javadsl

Interface RangeBasedProperty<T>


  • public interface RangeBasedProperty<T>
    Represents the value of a property together with the specific portion of the entity to which this range applies.

    An example of such a property is a speed limit of 30 km/h for the first half of a given key K, and 50 km/h for the second half.

      • containsOffset

        boolean containsOffset(double offset)
        Determines if an offset falls inside the range where this RangeBasedProperty applies.

        Note:
        Both start and end of this range are included.

        double end()
        The end relative offset. It must be in the [start; 1.0] range.

        The start relative offset. It must be in the [0.0; 1.0] range.
